In [22]:
# Getting training set

digit3_indexes = []
digit5_indexes = []

for i in range(len(train_Y)):
    if train_Y[i] == 3:
        digit3_indexes.append(i)
    elif train_Y[i] == 5:
        digit5_indexes.append(i)

digit3 = random.sample(digit3_indexes, 1000)
digit5 = random.sample(digit5_indexes, 1000)

train3_X = train_X[digit3]
train3_Y = train_Y[digit3]

train5_X = train_X[digit5]
train5_Y = train_Y[digit5]
In [23]:
# Getting test set

digit3_indexes = []
digit5_indexes = []

for i in range(len(test_Y)):
    if test_Y[i] == 3:
        digit3_indexes.append(i)
    elif test_Y[i] == 5:
        digit5_indexes.append(i)

digit3 = random.sample(digit3_indexes, 500)
digit5 = random.sample(digit5_indexes, 500)

test3_X = test_X[digit3]
test3_Y = test_Y[digit3]

test5_X = test_X[digit5]
test5_Y = test_Y[digit5]
In [24]:
# Combine

X_train = np.concatenate((train3_X, train5_X))
y_train = np.concatenate((train3_Y, train5_Y))

X_test = np.concatenate((test3_X, test5_X))
y_test = np.concatenate((test3_Y, test5_Y))
In [25]:
X_train = X_train.reshape(2000, -1)
X_test = X_test.reshape(1000, -1)

Q2¶

In [29]:
# PCA

K = [2, 5, 10, 20, 50, 100, 200]
train_accuracies = []
test_accuracies = []

for k in K:
    pca = PCA(n_components=k)
    pca.fit(X_train)
    # print(pca.explained_variance_)
    # print(pca.explained_variance_ratio_)
    # print(pca.components_)
    X_train_pca = pca.transform(X_train)
    X_test_pca = pca.transform(X_test)

    lr = LogisticRegression(C=100, random_state=0).fit(X_train_pca, y_train)
    train_accuracy = lr.score(X_train_pca, y_train)
    test_accuracy = lr.score(X_test_pca, y_test)
    
    train_accuracies.append(train_accuracy)
    test_accuracies.append(test_accuracy)
In [30]:
pd.DataFrame({'K':K, 'train':train_accuracies, 'test':test_accuracies})

Training accuracy keeps increasing until 1, testing accuracy increases as more components are added, but once there are many components, the LR starts to overfit, causing testing accuracy to decrease.

Generated images look somewhat like some of the digits, however, they are not the best. I guess it's because fitting to PPCA with only 2 components takes away some of the true data, and when you try to reconstruct the orginal data from the 2 components, it will never be as good as the original.
